RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 1M 70Y All Weather Track CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 28000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 If no three-year-olds are entered, older weight will revert to 122lbs. (If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf cour se, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at One Mile and Seventy Yards) (Rail at 28 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOTAL BLISS tracked in the five path, shifted into the three path and swept to the lead under a drive around the far turn, was headed by an outer foe passing the quarter pole and floated out to the six path into the lane, dug in thru the lane, brushed with the outer challenging foe near the sixteenth pole, but held on to win. GREY PRINCESS bumped with an inner foe at the start, chased in the four path, moved up under rousing around the far turn and bid passing the quarter pole, was floated out to the eight path into the stretch, ran on but drifted in thru the final furlong, brushed an inner foe late, and hung for place. GIRLY THE BUTCHER bumped with an inner foe at the start, rated in the five path and was under a ride into the far turn, ranged up nearing the quarter pole and was in the five path at the top of the stretch, tipped inwards thru the stretch, and kept on for show. MORGAN'S BLUFF broke out and bumped an outer foe, travelled off the pace in the two path, was receiving right handed cues around the far turn and was in the five path at the top of the lane, but was no factor. CAPPY got bumped on both sides at the start, raced in midpack around the two path, was asked for more into the far turn, but was empty around the four path turning into the stretch. KISS UPON A STAR set the pace in the two path rounding the first turn and tipped out to the four path into the backstretch, was under coaxing in the two path passing the three eighths marker, but abruptly gaveway. BLUEBERRY QUEEN bumped with an outer foe at the start, was steadied along the inside midway around the first turn, stalked around the three path down the backside but was done after a half.
